<p>Find the value of <m>k</m> so that the two lines are perpendicular.</p>

<p>Line 1 contains the points <m>($a, $b)</m> and <m>($line1x2, $line1y2)</m>. </p>
<p>Line 2 contains the points <m>($e, $f)</m> and <m>($line2x2, k)</m>. </p>



